Sql operation nodes contains operation type(join, scan...), its node id, its fragment id. The number on the arrow edge means how many rows output by child node. title: [Feature](remote)Remote Storage support single file when Cooldown.(FE)
body:
# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #14389

## Problem summary

Remote Storage support single file when Cooldown.
In old cooldown, one replica will create one remote file, it will create too many replicas in remote storage, because remote storage already support replicas.
In this case, several replicas in local files will upload to one file in remote storage.

## Description
In old case, 1 tablet has 3 replicas,  they are on BE1, BE2, BE3, when cooldowning, each replica will be uploaded as one replica on remote storage. As result, 1 tablet will create 3 replicas on remote storage.
But, remote storage has its own replica controller, 1 replica is enought.
So, this pr will create a policy, cooldown will create only 1 replica instead of 3 replicas.

This pr realize FE, FE will get replica cooldownType in tabletReport which is used to dicide which BE will used to upload file, others will only get meta from remote, but not upload file.

title: [improvement](ctas) use string type for varchar/char/string
body:
# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

## Problem summary

When executing `create table as select` stmt,
the varchar/char/string type of column in created table will be unified to `string` type.

Because when select from external table (mysql/pg, etc), the length of varchar in external database
is calculated by "char" length, not "byte" length.
So if there is a column with `varchar(10)` in external table, then there will be a same `varchar(10)`
in created table. But the byte length of data in external table may be larger than 10, causing failure of CTAS.

Change to string will not impact performance of the capacity of disk storage.
And notice that if a string type column is the first column, it will be changed to `varchar(65535)`,
because we do not allow string type column as sort key column.

# Proposed changes

~~Issue Number: close #xxx~~

## Problem summary

According to the description in [https://www.gnu.org/server/mirror.html](https://www.gnu.org/server/mirror.html), using the address `http://ftpmirror.gnu.org/` to download GNU packages is recommended. It can boost the download speed worldwide.

> Downloading from mirrors
First, for users/downloaders: the address http://ftpmirror.gnu.org/ multiplexes between the mirrors, trying to choose one that is nearby and up to date. E.g., http://ftpmirror.gnu.org/emacs/ goes to a mirror's directory of [GNU Emacs](https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/).
